extends base

block content

  h1.headerStyle Modules

  p The header module,  the featured sale module, the individual sale module within
    | the group sale module, and the footer module make up Gilt's site as the
    | most common modules.

  p The header always has the logo on the left, the header nav to right of the logo
    | account information, the cart icon, and the search bar on the right. The
    | background is black and the font is white, always. Code should match up with the code
    | previously written for the logo, header nav, and header search bar. In addition there is
    | a div where the user's account information goes.

  header.giltHeader
    h1.giltLogo Gilt
    nav.giltHeaderNav
      ul.giltHeaderList
        li Women
        li Men
        li Baby &amp; Kids
        li Home
        li City
        li Travel
    img.cartImg(src="images/cartImg.png")
    form
      input.giltHeaderSearch(type='text', placeholder='Search')

  p Note: for the header module this bit of code should be added so the category the
    | user is hovering on will underline in the accent color.

    pre
      code.language-css.
        .giltHeaderNav li:hover {
          border-bottom: 2px solid $primary-accent;
        }
  p Now the footer. The footer is similar to the header in that it has a $black background and
    | $white font. The footer is made up of another logo, a copyright, and then
    | several lists. It should look like this:

  footer.giltFooter
    h1.giltLogo Gilt
    ul.footerNav
      li Company
      li About
      li Press
      li Careers
      li Tech
      li Style Directory
    ul.footerNav
      li Customer Service
      li FAQ/ Contact Us
      li Return Policy
      li Shipping &amp; Tax
    ul.footerNav
      li Website Terms of Use
      li Privacy
      li Security
      li Terms of Service
    p.copy Â© 2007 - 2015 GILT GROUPE, INC.
      | ALL RIGHTS RESERVED.

  p While the code looks like this:

    pre
      code.language-css.
        .giltFooter {
          @include span-columns(12);
          background-color: $black;
          color: $white;
          padding: .8em;
        }

        .footerNav {
          @include span-columns (3);
          font-family: $primary-font;
          font-size: $regular-font;
        }

        .footerNav li {
          margin: .3em;
        }

        .footerNav li:first-child {
          font-weight: 700;
        }

        .footerNav li:hover {
          border-bottom: 2px solid $white;
        }

  p A featured sale is the sale that appears at the top of the main
    | page (under the header, of course) and on each category's main
    | sale page. This is the most popular sale or the sale we want users
    | to shop in.

    section.featuredSaleSection
      div.featuredSaleContent
        h1.saleh1 Choose Your Knives feat. Kyocera
        h2.saleh2 Upgrade your culinary routine with these well-made essentials
        button.shop-add-button-mod Shop this Sale

  p Include the shop-add-button discussed previously and the rest of the code should look like this:

  pre
    code.language-css.
      .featuredSaleSection {
        @include span-columns(12);
        padding: 1em;
        background-image: url(../images/featuredSale.jpg);
        background-repeat: no-repeat;
      }

      .featuredSaleContent {
        @include span-columns(5);
        @include shift(1 of 12);
        padding: .8em;
        color: $white;
        background-color: $black-opacity;
        border-radius: 1em;
      }

      .saleh1 {
        font-family: $secondary-font;
        font-size: $large-font;
      }

      .saleh2 {
        font-family: $italic-font;
        font-style: italic;
        font-size: $small-font;
      }
  p An individual sale module is pretty simple. It's just an image with a
    | header. It should link to the related sale.

    div.fontDiv.grid_12
      a.saleLink(href='http://www.gilt.com/sale/children/la-miniatura-for-girls-4494')
        h1.saleHeader La Minatura for Girls
        img(src='images/indiv-sale-img.jpg')

    pre
      code.language-css.
        .saleLink {
          @include span-columns(5);
          @include shift(1.5 of 5);
          background-color: $black-opacity;
        }

        .saleLink:hover {
          background-color: $primary-accent;
        }

        .saleHeader {
          font: $primary-font;
          font-size: $regular-font;
          color: $white;
          text-align: center;
          padding: .3em;
          margin: 0;
        }

        .saleLink img {
          @include span-columns(12);
        }

   p Use Neat combined with the indiviual sale modules to make a
    | sale section. That's all for modules!









